            . I am a constable. On the 30th of October, at half-past eight o'clock at night, I stopped the prisoner in High-street, Shadwell, with this curtain concealed under his jacket; he said it was his own, and he had had it six months, and had just redeemed it, over the water; but he could not tell me who the pawnbroker was, or where he himself lived.</p>
